The paper deals with a problem in metric space optimization, which is a common topic in computer science. The use of local search heuristics is also a common technique in algorithm design. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem also involves optimization and game theory, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a likely sub-category. The use of heuristics and approximation algorithms suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of lower bounds suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible sub-category.
